text: Saadia Sohail Rana (; born 23 April 1968) is a Pakistani politician who was a Member of the Provincial Assembly of the Punjab, from May 2013 to May 2018. ==Early life and education== She was born on 23 April 1968 in Lahore. She has the degree of Bachelor of Arts. ==Political career== She was elected to the Provincial Assembly of the Punjab as a candidate of Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf (PTI) on a reserved seat for women in 2013 Pakistani general election. She was re-elected to the Provincial Assembly of the Punjab as a candidate of PTI on a reserved seat for women in 2018 Pakistani general election. ==References== Category:Living people Category:Women members of the Provincial Assembly of the Punjab Category:Punjab MPAs 2013–2018 Category:1968 births Category:Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf MPAs (Punjab) Category:Punjab MPAs 2018–2023
title: Saadia Sohail Rana
